Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
justifyException(25.10)                                justifyException(25.10)

Name
       justifyException  -  Provides a debugging or justification mechanism of
       exceptions on ports

Syntax
       justifyException

       {-pins <pinList>}

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       {<partitionName> | <instanceName>}

       -view <viewName>

       [-help]

       Provides a debugging or justification mechanism of exceptions on ports.
       This command is used to debug exception constraints and justify all ex-
       ceptions on pins specified by -pins. To justify  exceptions,  you  must
       set  the  -justify parameter of the setBudgetingMode command to true to
       save the justify exception data during the deriveTimingBudget process.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs the command usage.

       <partitionName> | <instanceName>
              Specifies the name of the partition or instance to analyze.  The
              <instanceName> can only be specified when the deriveTimingBudget
              command  is  used  with  the  -inst option. In default partition
              mode, the <partitionName> is specified.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies the output file name that contains the justify  excep-
              tion  data for the instances or partitions specified by <instan-
              ceName> or <partitionName>. If you do not specify an output file
              using the -outfile parameter, the exception data  will  be  dis-
              played on the screen.

       -pins <pinList>
              Specifies  the  hierarchical  partition pins to be analyzed. You
              can use * to specify all pins.

       -view <viewName>
              Prints a report for the specified view.

Examples
              * The following command justifies exception for the  pins  input
                of  partition/instance partition1 and prints a report for view
                SETUP_VIEW1:

                justifyException partition1 -pins input -view SETUP_VIEW1

              * The following command justifies exception for all pins of  the
                partition/instance  partition1  and  prints  a report for view
                HOLD_VIEW1 in the file justfyData:

                justifyException partition1 -pins * -outfile justifydata -view
                HOLD_VIEW1

